l></mjx-container></p>
<p>The standard deviation, <em data-effect=3D"italics">=CF=83</em>, is the =
same as the mean. <em data-effect=3D"italics">=CE=BC</em> =3D <em data-effe=
ct=3D"italics">=CF=83</em></p>
<p id=3D"fs-idp111556368">The distribution notation is <em data-effect=3D"i=
talics">X</em> ~ <em data-effect=3D"italics">Exp</em>(<em data-effect=3D"it=
alics">m</em>). Therefore, <em data-effect=3D"italics">X</em> ~ <em data-ef=
fect=3D"italics">Exp</em>(0.25).</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idm18148336" class=3D"finger">The probability density function =
is <em data-effect=3D"italics">f</em>(<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em>) =
=3D <em data-effect=3D"italics">me</em><sup>=E2=80=93<em data-effect=3D"ita=
lics">mx</em></sup>. The number <em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em> =3D 2.71=
828182846=E2=80=A6 It is a number that is used often in mathematics. Scient=
ific calculators have the key =E2=80=9C<em data-effect=3D"italics">e<sup>x<=
/sup></em>.=E2=80=9D If you enter one for <em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em=
>, the calculator will display the value <em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em>=
.</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idm74833712">The curve is:</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idp44233136"><em data-effect=3D"italics">f</em>(<em data-effect=
=3D"italics">x</em>) =3D 0.25<em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em><sup>=E2=80=
=930.25<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em></sup> where <em data-effect=3D"it=
alics">x</em> is at least zero and <em data-effect=3D"italics">m</em> =3D 0=
.25.</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idp127275616">For example, <em data-effect=3D"italics">f</em>(5=
) =3D 0.25<em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em><sup>=E2=88=92(0.25)(5)</sup> =
=3D 0.072. The postal clerk spends five minutes with the customers.&nbsp;Th=
e graph is as follows:</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idm23774336"><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://s3-us-west-=
2.amazonaws.com/courses-images/wp-content/uploads/sites/132/2016/04/2121444=
9/fig-ch05_04_01N.jpg" alt=3D"Exponential graph with increments of 2 from 0=
-20 on the x-axis of =CE=BC =3D 4 and increments of 0.05 from 0.05-0.25 on =
the y-axis of m =3D 0.25. The curved line begins at the top at point (0, 0.=
25) and curves down to point (20, 0). The x-axis is equal to a continuous r=
andom variable." width=3D"380" data-media-type=3D"image/jpg"></p>
<div id=3D"fs-idp58220144" class=3D"example" data-type=3D"example">
<section tabindex=3D"-1" class=3D" focusable">
<p id=3D"fs-idm725296">Notice the graph is a declining curve. When <em data=
-effect=3D"italics">x</em> =3D 0,</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idm61837632"><em data-effect=3D"italics">f</em>(<em data-effect=
=3D"italics">x</em>) =3D 0.25<em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em><sup>(=E2=88=
=920.25)(0)</sup> =3D (0.25)(1) =3D 0.25 =3D <em data-effect=3D"italics">m<=
/em>. The maximum value on the <em data-effect=3D"italics">y</em>-axis is <=
em data-effect=3D"italics">m</em>.</p>
</section>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"fs-idm39150960" class=3D"note statistics try ui-has-child-title"=
 data-type=3D"note" data-has-label=3D"true" data-label=3D"">
<header>
<div class=3D"textbox key-takeaways"></div>
</header>
<header>
<h3 class=3D"title" data-type=3D"title">Try It</h3>
</header>
<section tabindex=3D"-1" class=3D" focusable">
<div id=3D"fs-idm37492592" class=3D"exercise" data-type=3D"exercise">
<section tabindex=3D"-1" class=3D" focusable">
<div id=3D"fs-idp79313392" class=3D"problem" data-type=3D"problem">
<p id=3D"fs-idm18125728">The amount of time spouses shop for anniversary ca=
rds can be modeled by an exponential distribution with the average amount o=
f time equal to eight minutes. Write the distribution, state the probabilit=
y density function, and graph the distribution.</p>
<p>Solution:</p>
<p><em data-effect=3D"italics">X</em> ~ <em data-effect=3D"italics">Exp</em=
>(0.125); <em data-effect=3D"italics">f</em>(<em data-effect=3D"italics">x<=
/em>) =3D 0.125e<sup>=E2=80=930.125<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em></sup>=
;</p>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/course=
s-images/wp-content/uploads/sites/132/2016/04/21214451/CNX_Stats_C05_M04_tr=
yit001annoN.jpg" alt=3D"" width=3D"380" data-media-type=3D"image/jpg"></p>
</div>
</section>
</div>
</section>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<section tabindex=3D"-1" class=3D" focusable">
<div id=3D"fs-idm37492592" class=3D"exercise" data-type=3D"exercise">
<section tabindex=3D"-1" class=3D" focusable">
<div id=3D"fs-idp79313392" class=3D"problem" data-type=3D"problem">
<div class=3D"textbox exercises">
<div id=3D"fs-idp79313392" class=3D"problem" data-type=3D"problem">
<h3>&nbsp;Example</h3>
<p>Using the information in example 1, find the probability that a clerk sp=
ends four to five minutes with a randomly selected customer.</p>
<p>The curve is:</p>
<p><em data-effect=3D"italics">X</em> ~ <em data-effect=3D"italics">Exp</em=
>(0.125); <em data-effect=3D"italics">f</em>(<em data-effect=3D"italics">x<=
/em>) =3D 0.125e<sup>=E2=80=930.125<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em></sup>=
</p>
<p id=3D"fs-idp81828496">a) Find <em data-effect=3D"italics">P</em>(4 &lt; =
<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em> &lt; 5).</p>
<p data-type=3D"newline">Solution:</p>
<div data-type=3D"newline">The <strong>cumulative distribution function (CD=
F)</strong> gives the area to the left.</div>
<div data-type=3D"newline"><em data-effect=3D"italics">P</em>(<em data-effe=
