t=3D"italics">X</em> &gt; 5) =3D 1 =E2=80=93 <em data-effect=3D"italics">P<=
/em>(<em data-effect=3D"italics">X</em> &lt; 5) =3D 1 =E2=80=93 (1 =E2=80=
=93 <em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em><sup>(=E2=80=935)(0.5)</sup>) =3D e<s=
up>=E2=80=932.5</sup> =E2=89=88 0.0821.</div>
</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://courses.candelalearning.com/masterystats1x6xmaster/w=
p-content/uploads/sites/419/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-15-at-2.02.27-PM.pn=
g"><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"aligncenter size-full =
wp-image-716" src=3D"https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/courses-images/wp-c=
ontent/uploads/sites/132/2016/04/21214506/Screen-Shot-2015-06-15-at-2.02.27=
-PM.png" alt=3D"Graph of 1-(1-e^(-0.5x)) with probability P(x &lt; 5) shade=
d" width=3D"385" height=3D"216"></a></li>
<li>We want to solve 0.70 =3D <em data-effect=3D"italics">P</em>(<em data-e=
ffect=3D"italics">X</em> &lt; <em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em>) for <em d=
