Substituting in the cumulative distribution function gives 0.70 =3D 1 =E2=
=80=93 <em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em><sup>=E2=80=930.5<em data-effect=
=3D"italics">x</em></sup>, so that <em data-effect=3D"italics">e</em><sup>=
=E2=80=930.5x</sup> =3D 0.30. Converting this to logarithmic form gives =E2=
=80=930.5<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</em> =3D <em data-effect=3D"italics"=
>ln</em>(0.30), or <span class=3D"MathJax"><span class=3D"math"><span class=
